The Slovak unit of  Volkswagen AG (VOW) 
will hold companywide vacation between July 18 and July 31, the
automaker said today in a statement.  During the break, the factory in the Slovak capital,
Bratislava, will still continue preparations for serial
production of the so-called new small family cars, which is
scheduled to begin later this year, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Radoslav Tomek in Bratislava at 
 rtomek@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net . 